reviews.text: Beautiful ambiance all around. You could have mistaken the Murray is in Manhattan somewhere. Don’t bother with the food items on the menu. Tried the teriyaki chicken, Murray burger and the Curry. For the price we expect a lot more quality. $400/head should buy you more.
Went for a meeting. Didnt eat. Very nice atmosphere. Only problem is the air conditioning was way way too strong.

Had lunch at Garden Lounge, The Murray; Hong Kong island's newest five star hotel. 

The ginger and carrot soup went down very well as did the fish. The lamb curry is worth ordering for the impressive presentation alone. 

Nice, open layout and a few tables outside, staff were professional and courteous without being over the top. 

A Western and Asian menu with prices ranging from HK$150 for the soup of the day to HK$350 plus for a mains and a 10 percent service charge on top. Air conditioning was fierce.

For HKD300pax it’s not a bad deal.. but the flavours weren’t as good as expected. The sandwiches and crepe were bland, the cookie had no taste, I could keep going on. But for this price, I suppose I’m just paying for the environment. Still the service was nice, just that they have a time limit and wouldn’t let you sit and chat for long ... then why bother going for high tea? 
Unfortunately I won’t come back for sure :(
Relaxing environment of afternoon tea experience. I love the design of the hotel and would recommend to seat near the window side.

reviews.text:
absolutely superb hotel.  Hong Kong's current best.  the rooms are stunning.  beautiful new fixtures and fittings.  the bathroom and shower to die for.  the views are phenomenal.  love the bar downstairs and have frequented often.  great place to have a drink.  the bartender is a superstar.  will be back for drinks and meals.  and may again to stay.  A special thanks to Christopher
Frederic 
And anna who made each of my three stays seamless

TERRIFIC MODERN HOTEL WITH INCREDIBLE SERVICE

Stayed at the Murray last month and what a pleasant surprise.  The rooms are exceptional - clean, modern, very tasteful, filled with conveniences.  The staff is knowledgeable, friendly and attentive.  The bar is excellent and the second floor Garden Lounge became a second office.  Also, very, very well located in Central.  Only downside is that the gym/workout space is very small.  But this will be my new go-to hotel in HK.

Staying here at the moment. 
Gorgeous hotel. 
Super expensive. 
Really disappointed with the level of service at breakfast. 
My husband ordered a simple fruit platter. 
20 mins later it hadn’t arrived. 
We needed to be somewhere so couldn’t wait any longer. 
Lots of staff buzzing around but no one aware of customer service. 
Put a damper on such a lovely premises.

Incredible service, huge rooms in a historic mod building that is at once close to everything and also just removed enough to abut a beautiful downtown park. A top-class new hotel at much lower rates than its 5-star competitors.

We had been at the roof too bar. Nice ambience in evening when we were around. Loved the view of the skyline and harbour on one side and the peak on other side. Mostly had drink's so please pardon for limited review post. Nice place to spend an evening with friends.

reviews.text:
香港のセントラル
香港公園の手前にある
古いオフィスビルを
フルリノベーションした
高級ホテル

スタッフのサービス、ロビーの雰囲気
部屋の備品、部屋の設備
何もかもが洗練されている。

重厚でモダン、清潔感がある。

セントラルのMTR駅からは少し歩くが
散歩だと思えばたいした距離ではない。

今回宿泊したのはデラックスルーム
キングサイズベッドであるが、
窓が二面あり部屋がとても明るく
広々としている。

また香港公園や香港の山々の借景が素晴らししい。

携帯やスマホ、モバイルバッテリー、PCの
充電設備も最新で、USBコネクタが直接させるようになっている。

部屋の水回りの金具類やシャワーは全てGOLD。

金融街であること、また金運UPにかけた
香港のユーモアかもしれない。

水回りの床や壁は全て大理石。
しかしシャワーのところだけは
滑り止めで大理石の床に溝が彫られているので
安心してシャワーが楽しめる。
ただ一つ欲を言うなら、
シャワーの水圧がもう少し強ければ尚良い。
